citeinfo.title: Environmentally_Sensitive_Areas

descript.abstract: This dataset is a combination of several elements of environmentally sensitive areas. Those elements are (1) Multiple Species Conservation Program (MSCP) hardline designations, (2) MSCP preserved land, (3) MSCP pre-approved mitigation area designations, (4) water bodies listed in the California Water Resources Control Board 2006 Clean Water Act section 303(d), (5) rare waters, and (6) areas of significant biological concern.
descript.purpose: This dataset was developed to show areas of environmentally sensitive areas within the unincorporated parts of San Diego county.
